The '''Movement for a Europe of Liberties and Democracy''' ({{lang-fr|Mouvement pour l'Europe des libertés et de la démocratie}}), abbreviated to '''MELD''', was a [[national conservatism|national-conservative]]<ref name="Nordsieck"/> [[European political party|political party at European level]] founded in 2011, composed of parties belonging to the [[Europe of Freedom and Democracy]] (EFD) group in the European Parliament, with the notable absence of the [[UK Independence Party]], which was a member of the EFD, but not of the MELD. In 2012, MELD received a grant from the European Parliament of €621,482.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.europarl.europa.eu/pdf/grants/grant_amounts_parties_01-03-2012.pdf |title=Grants from the European Parliament to political parties at European level 2004-2012 |author=Political Structures Financing Unit |date=March 2012 |work= |publisher=European Parliament |accessdate=26 August 2012}}</ref>  Its affiliated [[political foundation at European level|political foundation]]  was the [[Foundation for a Europe of Liberties and Democracy]] (FELD), which received a grant of €412,361.  Both were headquartered at 18, rue Cler, in [[Paris]], [[France]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.europarl.europa.eu/pdf/grants/grant_amounts_foundations_per_01-03-2012.pdf |title=Grants from the European Parliament to political foundations at European level 2008-2012 |author=Political Structures Financing Unit |date=March 2012 |work= |publisher=European Parliament |accessdate=26 August 2012}}</ref> The president of the party was [[Jacek Wlosowicz]].

MELD was dissolved in 2015 by the [[European Parliament]] due to misuse of EU funding.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://euobserver.com/institutional/133377|title=Danish far-right MEP ordered to return €400,000|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.politico.eu/article/eu-funding-scandal-threatens-to-engulf-polish-government/|title=Polish minister faces call to quit over party funding|date=18 November 2016|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/justice-home-affairs/news/eu-parliament-tells-mep-to-pay-back-eu-funding-worth-e400000/|title=European Parliament tells MEP to return €400,000|date=6 May 2016|publisher=}}</ref>

